This directory contains a custom app-specific OS designed to run "libevent"
based services extremely efficiently. Currently it requires a static library
for Intel DPDK and a compatible Intel NIC (e.g. 82599, X540 etc.)

Build Instructions
==================

1.) Set up DPDK... Detailed instructions are available here:
http://www.intel.com/content/dam/www/public/us/en/documents/guides/intel-dpdk-getting-started-guide.pdf

Here's the quick version...
- unpack and cd to dpdk
$ make config T=x86_64-default-linuxapp-gcc
$ make
$ modprobe uio
$ insmod build/kmod/igb_uio.ko
$ mkdir -p /mnt/huge
$ mount -t hugetlbfs nodev /mnt/hugetlbfs
$ echo 64 > /sys/devices/system/node/node0/hugepages/hugepages-2048kB/nr_hugepages





